 British-South African actress Anna Karen, best known as Olive from the sitcom On the buses, passed away at the age of 85.  She died in a fire in her house.    The circumstances surrounding last night’s fire were not suspicious at first glance, police said BBC News†  About twenty firefighters were needed to extinguish the fire.  The actress died on the spot. “I have just heard the terrible news that my wonderful friend Anna Karen has died in a house fire,” tweeted singer Cheryl Baker, who won the Eurovision Song Contest in 1981 with Bucks Fizz.  ‘What a horrible way to die, I can’t think of it.  I loved her, she was a special person, on TV and off.’ Karen played in all seven seasons of the well-known series between 1969 and 1973 On the buses†  Viewers were able to draw out the character Olive Rudge with her wig and eye-catching glasses, a look that Karen herself said made her “the ugliest woman on TV.” She later played the character again in the sitcom The rag trade†  Karen, who was born Ann McCall in South Africa and came to England when she was seventeen, also played for many years in the famous soap eastenders†   Also listen to the AD Media Podcast:   Unfortunately, we cannot show this social post, live blog or otherwise because it contains one or more social media elements.  Accept the social media cookies to still show this content.    Watch our Show & Entertainment videos below:  Free unlimited access to Showbytes?  Which can!  Log in or create an account and never miss a thing from the stars.  Yes, I want free unlimited access On the buses actress Anna Karen dies in fire: ‘Terrible way to die’ |  show
